Portfolio Website - GitHub Repository
📌 Task Objectives
This repository contains a professional portfolio website that serves as an online resume, showcasing:
1) Personal introduction and background
2) Technical and professional skills
3) Project portfolio with descriptions
4) Contact form functionality
5) Fully responsive design

https://github.com/789478/Portfolio--Website/blob/main/Nitu%20Sharma%20_%20Portfolio.mp4

🛠️ Technologies Used
HTML5
CSS3 (Flexbox, Grid)
JavaScript (ES6+)
Git/GitHub for version control

✨ Key Features
Modern UI Design: Clean, professional layout with animations
Responsive: Works on all device sizes
Interactive Elements: Smooth scrolling, form validation
Performance Optimized: Fast loading with optimized assets
Accessible: Semantic HTML and ARIA attributes

🏃‍♂️ How to Run Locally
Prerequisites
Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
Code editor (VS Code recommended)
Git (optional)

Installation
1) Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/portfolio-website.git

2) Navigate to project directory:
cd portfolio-website

3) Open index.html in your browser

🏗️ Project Structure
portfolio-website/
├── index.html          # Main HTML file
├── css/
│   ├── style.css       # Main styles
│   └── animations.css  # Animation styles
├── js/
│   ├── main.js         # Core functionality
│   └── form-handler.js # Contact form handling
├── images/             # All project images
└── README.md           # This file

